<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Buck</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September 23,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 424.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 672, of the 18th ultimo, in regard to the arbitration of the
                            house-tax question.</p>
                        <p>The assurance you report as having received from the minister of foreign
                            affairs that the further collection of this tax will be suspended
                            pending the decision of the arbitral court is an apparently satisfactory
                            result of your suggestions in pursuance of telegraphic instructions of
                            January 18 last, to which you refer.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>